-- Hungary Stocks: OTP Bank, FHB Are Active in Budapest Trading
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-03-08T16:20:19Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-08/hungary-stocks-otp-bank-fhb-are-active-in-budapest-trading.html
Hungary ’s benchmark BUX stock index
rose 0.4 percent to 18,582.69 by the close in Budapest.  The following were among the most active equities in the
Hungarian market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  OTP Bank Nyrt. (OTP)  , Hungary’s largest lender, rose for
the first time in four days as a deadline on  Greece ’s debt swap
approached and Hungary’s government pledged to obtain aid. The
shares gained as much as 3.3 percent and ended 0.3 percent
higher at 3,700 forint.  Foldhitel es Jelzalogbank Nyrt.  (FHB HB), a Hungarian
mortgage lender known as FHB, rose 4.8 percent to 563 forint.
Hungary’s government and commercial banks agreed to limit the
scope of a plan allowing foreign-currency loan holders to
temporarily service their debt at lower exchange rates.  Egis Nyrt. (EGIS)  , a Hungarian drugmaker owned by
Laboratoires Servier, rose for a second day after Erste Group
Bank AG upgraded its recommendation on the stock to buy from
accumulate. The shares advanced as much as 1.8 percent, before
closing 0.4 percent higher at 15,525 forint.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
